 ### Use Dictionary Alternate Lookup for Span-Based Keys
 🟡 **DO** use `GetAlternateLookup<ReadOnlySpan<char>>()` to avoid string allocation on lookups | .NET 9+

 ❌
 ```csharp
 string key = headerLine.Substring(0, colonIndex);
